wikipedia_page.main: George William Webb (23 October 1857 – 26 December 1931) was an English professional cricketer, umpire and cricket coach. Webb played in two first-class cricket matches for Kent County Cricket Club.

George Webbe (1856 – 7 June 1934) was a New Zealand cricketer who played three first-class matches for Wellington. He was born in Galway, Ireland, and died in Levin, New Zealand.
